subject: not a valid XML document. It is possibly corrupted
msgSnippet: I m using JUnit 3.8.1 on cygwin with ant 1.5.1, java jdk1.4.1-b21. Junitreport reports: [junitreport] [Fatal Error] :-1:-1: Premature end of file.
messageBody:
I'm using JUnit 3.8.1 on cygwin with ant 1.5.1, java jdk1.4.1-b21.
Junitreport reports:
[junitreport] [Fatal Error] :-1:-1: Premature end of file.
[junitreport] The file xml\TEST-PeopleTest.xml is not a valid XML document. It is possibly corrupted.
[junitreport] [Fatal Error] TEST-CategoriesTest.xml:179:1: Content is not allowed in trailing section.
[junitreport] The file CategoriesTest.xml is not a valid XML document. It is possibly corrupted.

The file TEST-PeopleTest.xml is empty and
the last few lines of the generated TEST-CategoriesTest.xml file are:

</error>
</testcase>
<testcase name="testSetGet_Sorted" time="0.0"></testcase>
<testcase name="testVault" time="0.0"></testcase>
<system-out><![CDATA[]]></system-out>
<system-err><![CDATA[]]></system-err>
</testsuite>
>



The line after </testsuite> is suspicious. Any idea what is causing it?
When JUnit is running CategoryTest,
[junit] Running CategoryTest
[junit] Tests run: 12, Failures: 0, Errors: 9, Time elapsed: 2.313 sec

Does anyone have any idea what's wrong?
Thanks for your help,
Steve Kelem
